// chase.su — value-feedback read head (pointer-chase).
// planning/sutra-spec/ram-pointers.md.
//
// Each RAM cell is a complex number: real = codepoint, imag = next
// address. The orchestrator reads the cell at the current address and
// passes it as `served`; this head carries it through the substrate and
// re-emits it, so the orchestrator can decode BOTH the payload (real)
// and the next address (imag) from a value that genuinely transited the
// substrate. The visited address chain is determined by RAM contents
// fed back through the substrate — data-dependent addressing, the
// defining NTM read capability. `steps` is a substrate-side counter of
// how many cells were read.
function vector chase(vector served) {
    recurring vector steps = make_real(0.0);
    recur(steps + make_real(1.0));
    return(served);
}

function string main() { return "ok"; }
